The paper deals with measuring randomness in images, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of Shannon entropy also suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the optimization of parameters and statistical tests indicate a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
